      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed on the pedicle screw–rod assembly. Stiffness and yield force QoIs changed by less than 1.5% between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation confirmed discretization error well within acceptance bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Force and displacement residuals converge to < 0.1% of applied load; energy balance monitored each increment.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver convergence was confirmed for each load step. Residual norms and energy balance checks are archived. No divergence or spurious hourglassing observed across the ensemble runs."
